%Steps%

1. If you have not already, download the [](Resources\ContentExamples) project from the Unreal Engine Launcher.

1. Open the **Content Examples** project.
	
	![](CE_Start.png)(w:500)

1. Click on **File > Open Level**.

1. Select the **VR.umap**, then click **Open**.

	![](VRmap.png)

1. Click on the arrow next to **Play** in the **Level Editor Toolbar** to open the **Play In Editor** options.

	![](PlayDropdown.png)

1. Select the **VR Preview** option and then put the HMD on.

	![](StandAloneGame.png)

	[REGION:tip]
	You can use the **Standalone Game** option but if you do make sure to press **Alt+Enter** to enter VR mode. If you do not do this you will not see anything when you put the HMD on.
	[/REGION]

1. With the HMD on you should now something similar to the image below being displayed in the HMD.

	![](VRMode.png)(w:800)

1. To end game play you can do either of the following two options.

	* Press **~** and type **Quit** in the console
	* Press **Shift+F1** to reclaim your mouse cursor and close the window.


